caption.p: Temporal profiles of cytokines and growth factors in cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). Levels of interleukin (IL)‐6, transforming growth factor (TGF)‐β1/2, tumor necrosis factor (TNF)‐α, IL‐1β, vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF), fibroblast growth factor (FGF), and brain‐derived neurotropic factor (BDNF), in CSF obtained before MSC transplantation, and at 36–40 weeks CA, are shown for each infant transplanted with MSCs. * p < .05; Abbreviations: CA 36–40w, corrected age of 36–40 weeks. Pre, pre‐MSCs transplantation.
